{"article_id":"aK5ZvWSrp8Vldb8h","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"In a dramatic turnaround , President Obama said Saturday","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"that he will wait for congressional authorization","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"to punish Syria for a chemical weapons attack ,","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"even though he has decided","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"a military strike is needed .","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"\" We should have this debate , \"","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"the president said in an announcement in the White House Rose Garden .","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"\" I respect the views of those","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"who call for caution . \"","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"After more than a week of deliberation , Mr. Obama essentially put the onus on Congress","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"to stop him from launching missile strikes against targets of the regime of Syrian President Bashar Assad .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"Lawmakers are not scheduled to return from their August recess until Sept. 9 .","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"\" I have decided","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"that the United States should take military action against Syrian regime targets , \"","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"Mr. Obama said ,","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"adding","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"that he intends such action to be \" limited in duration and scope . \"","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"With Vice President Joseph R. Biden at his side , Mr. Obama said ,","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"\" I ' m confident","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"we can hold the Assad regime accountable for their use of chemical weapons ,","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"deter this kind of behavior ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"and degrade their capacity","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"to carry it out . \"","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"The president said","depth":4},{"id":24,"text":"U.S. military forces are positioned in the region","depth":5},{"id":25,"text":"to strike at his command .","depth":5},{"id":26,"text":"SEE ALSO :","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"ANALYSIS :","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"Isolated Obama turns to Congress for support","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"\" The chairman of the Joint Chiefs has informed me","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"that we are prepared to strike","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"whenever we choose , \"","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"Mr. Obama said .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"\" Moreover , the chairman has indicated to me","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"that our capacity","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"to execute this mission","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"is not time-sensitive","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":";","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"it will be effective tomorrow , or next week , or one month from now .","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"And I ' m prepared to give that order . \"","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"But he said","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"he has consulted again with congressional leaders Saturday morning","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"and will wait for lawmakers to vote on military action .","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"The Democratic and Republican leaders of both the House and Senate have agreed to hold a debate and vote on a Syrian military strike ,","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"the president said .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"\" While I believe","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"I have the authority","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"to carry out this military action","depth":14},{"id":48,"text":"without specific congressional authorization ,","depth":14},{"id":49,"text":"I know","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"that the country will be stronger","depth":14},{"id":51,"text":"if we take this course ,","depth":14},{"id":52,"text":"and our actions will be even more effective , \"","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"the president said .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"\" Today I ' m asking Congress to send a message to the world . \"","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"The announcement appears to delay any U.S. military move for 10 days or more .","depth":5},{"id":56,"text":"House GOP Speaker John Boehner and the chamber ' s top Republicans immediately issued a joint statement","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"praising Mr. Obama ' s decision","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"to consult Congress","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"and saying","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"the House would hold its vote","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"when Congress returns to work .","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"\" Under the Constitution , the responsibility","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"to declare war","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"lies with Congress , \"","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"the House GOP leaders said .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"\" We are glad","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"the president is seeking authorization for any military action in Syria in response to serious , substantive questions","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"being raised .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"In consultation with the president , we expect the House to consider a measure the week of September 9th . \"","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"The announcement came as a surprise","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"because Mr. Obama had been signaling for the past several days","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"that he intends to send a \" shot across the bow \" to the Syrian regime .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"He said Friday","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"he was contemplating \" limited \" action against Syria .","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"For the past week , administration officials have deflected questions","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"about seeking congressional authorization for military action ,","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"saying only","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"that Mr. Obama was willing to \" consult \" lawmakers .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"While the GOP suggested","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"that Mr. Obama still has a burden of proof","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"to overcome","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"about protecting U.S. national-security interests ,","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"the president said","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"lawmakers now bear responsibility","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"for upholding international rules against wartime atrocities .","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"\" What message will we send","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"if a dictator can gas hundreds of children to death in plain sight","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"and pay no price ? \"","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"Mr. Obama asked .","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"\" If we won ' t enforce accountability in the face of this heinous act ,","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"what does it say about our resolve","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"to stand up to others","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"who flout fundamental international rules ? \"","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"The president ' s announcement came","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"only hours after UN inspectors left Syria","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"after investigating the aftermath of the suspected chemical weapons attacks on Aug. 21","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"that killed more than 1,400 civilians ,","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"said to be perpetrated by elements of the Assad regime .","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"The inspectors will share their findings with UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon ,","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"who has said","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"he wants to wait","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"until a final report is completed","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"before presenting it to the UN Security Council","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"- which could take a week .","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"The Obama administration has said","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"there ' s no point","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"in waiting for the UN","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"because Russia would veto any proposed punishment for Syria .","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"Mr. Obama said of the U.N. ,","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"\" I ' m comfortable going forward","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"without the approval of a United Nations Security Council","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"that , so far , has been completely paralyzed and unwilling to hold Assad accountable . \"","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"A U.N. spokesman said","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"it was \" grotesque \" to speculate that the organization ' s weapons inspectors left Syria early Saturday","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"to give room for the U.S. to launch an attack .","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"An unnamed Syrian security official told the AFP news agency","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"that Syria was \" ready to retaliate at any moment \" to any attack by the U.S .","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"Mr. Obama and Secretary of State John F. Kerry said Friday","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"the U.S. had convincing proof via intelligence and witness accounts","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"that Mr. Assad ' s military was responsible for the chemical attack ,","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"citing detailed evidence of the rocket barrages","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"that targeted 12 neighborhoods east of Damascus .","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"Mr. Kerry , in particular , was very forceful in his accusations .","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"Mr. Obama was more reserved about a possible \" limited \" military response ,","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"and spoke of the public ' s war-weariness , and his own .","depth":7},{"id":126,"text":"The president ' s comments came after more than a week of deliberations","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"in which he sought the support of allies such as Britain and France ,","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"and consulted with congressional leaders .","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"The British Parliament voted on Thursday not to participate with the U.S. in any military action against Syria ;","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"French President Francois Holland voiced his support for a move .","depth":7},{"id":131,"text":"The White House also has scheduled a classified briefing with key lawmakers in Congress for 2 p.m. Sunday .","depth":5},{"id":132,"text":"An anticipated attack by the U.S. has prompted concerns about Syria ' s potential responses .","depth":6},{"id":133,"text":"Israel has canceled weekend leave for its military members ,","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"and Israelis have been lining up for hours","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"to obtain government-issued gas masks .","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"As the president spoke ,","depth":6},{"id":137,"text":"demonstrators could be heard outside the north fence of the White House ,","depth":7},{"id":138,"text":"shouting \" hands off Syria \" and other slogans .","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"After he concluded his remarks Saturday ,","depth":5},{"id":140,"text":"Mr. Obama ignored a question from the press after his remarks","depth":6},{"id":141,"text":"about whether he would move forward","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"if Congress did not authorize a strike .","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"About 25 minutes after concluding his remarks ,","depth":5},{"id":144,"text":"Mr. Obama departed the White House with Mr. Biden in a motorcade","depth":6},{"id":145,"text":"to play golf at Fort Belvoir in suburban Virginia .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":291,"left":171,"right":290,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":171,"left":154,"right":170,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":150,"right":153,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":148,"right":149,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":0,"right":147,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":147,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":153,"left":151,"right":152,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":170,"left":167,"right":169,"relation":"elaboration","nu